[sound prompt to start speaking]

32
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,340
Let's begin!

33
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:19,380
You're done!

34
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,820
Congratulations!

35
00:04:22,019 --> 00:04:26,440
By the way, the /æ/ is almost always written as the letter 'a.'

36
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,820
And more on the spelling:

37
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:38,920
the letter 'a' stands for the /æ/ sound, as in the word "cat," in 97% of cases.

38
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:43,080
The remaining 3% are split between the combination of letters

39
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,900
'al,'  as in the word "half,"

40
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,420
and 'au,' as in the word "laugh."

41
